      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "manual_contract_registry_pattern"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "mutable_global_catalog_state",
      "summary": "Catalog definitions are stored in package-level mutable vars, enabling hidden cross-file state coupling.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/startram_contracts.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Both files define catalog entries and catalog spec slices as `var` values (`protocol...Contract`, `protocolContractCatalogSpecs`, `startram...Contract`, `startramContractCatalogSpecs`).",
        "Any file in the same package can mutate these vars at runtime, which makes contract boundary behavior depend on import/runtime state rather than immutable declarations."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Make catalog state immutable: use package-level arrays/constants where possible, return constructed copies from functions, and prevent direct mutable global registry storage.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "manual_contract_registry_pattern"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "inconsistent_contract_surface_conventions",
      "summary": "Sibling contract modules expose inconsistent API surfaces, which weakens boundary predictability across the contracts subsystem.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/startram_contracts.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`protocol_contracts.go` publishes duplicated alias layers (`protocol...` constants, exported `Upload...` constants, and extra lower-case aliases for introduced/compatibility metadata).",
        "`startram_contracts.go` exports only `APIConnectionError` while keeping equivalent metadata constants private, indicating no consistent module contract for what should be externally visible."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define and enforce a single exposure convention for contract modules (for example: export only contract IDs, keep metadata internal, and expose metadata via a common query API) and normalize both files to that policy.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "manual_contract_registry_pattern"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Contract catalogs are authored through repeated manual patterns instead of one subsystem-level registration abstraction.",
      "Boundary policy for what a contract module should expose is undocumented or unenforced."
    ],
